Type: Package
Package: ClinicoPathDescriptives
Title: Descriptive Analysis for Clinicopathological Research
Version: 1.0.0
Date: 2026-07-13
Authors@R: person(given = "Serdar", family = "Balci", role = c("aut",
 "cre", "cph"), email = "serdarbalci@serdarbalci.com", comment =
 c(ORCID = "0000-0002-7852-3851"))
Maintainer: Serdar Balci <serdarbalci@serdarbalci.com>
Description: A comprehensive toolkit for descriptive analysis in
 clinicopathological research. Provides interactive graphical
 user interface functions through the 'jamovi' statistical
 platform. Features include generating descriptive summaries in
 natural language, creating cross tables with appropriate
 statistical tests, performing survival analyses with tables and
 plots, visualizing categorical data relationships through
 alluvial diagrams and Venn diagrams, and conducting data
 quality assessments using Benford's law. The package emphasizes
 reproducible research workflows and automated reporting
 capabilities for medical research. For comments, suggestions,
 feature requests or reporting bugs, please open an issue at
 <https://github.com/sbalci/ClinicoPathDescriptives/issues/>.
